  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The integration of TiO 2 -based photosensitizers for thiazine dye removal and reuse holds promise for advancing efficient and eco-friendly wastewater treatment strategies.",
    "The mechanisms of light absorption and energy transfer between dye sensitizers and TiO 2 involve a series of intricate steps that facilitate the enhancement of photocatalytic activity.",
    "For example, organic dye, as a photosensitizer, absorbs light energy, typically in the visible spectrum (Zani et al., 2021).",
    "This absorbed energy excites the electrons within the dye molecules to higher energy states.",
    "Subsequently, the excited electrons in organic dye are transferred to the TiO 2 surface through a process known as energy transfer."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, organic dye, as a photosensitizer, absorbs light energy, typically in the visible spectrum (Zani et al., 2021)."
  ]
}